data.title: Olympic Track And Field Results on Aug. 4: Morning Session
data.meta_description: Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, Femke Bol, Gabby Thomas, Grant Holloway cruise in opening rounds.
data.text:
More of the stars came out in Day 3 of Olympic track and field action as medal favorites Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, Gabby Thomas, Grant Holloway, and Femke Bol made debuts in their respective individual events. All four stars qualified for the next round with ease. One bit of news was the surprise scratch in the Women's 200m from Jamaica's Shericka Jackson, the reigning World Champion in the event.
